<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
examined at least two specimens of both sexes (see the simbols male and female in the first couplet). However, in the original description 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
(in Radoszkowski) gave the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum simile" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Hedychrum simile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sub 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">cyaneum</emphasis>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
nec 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Brullé">Brulle</normalizedToken>
) based only on the male housed in the Radoszkowski collection and dissected by the Russian entomologist, who drew the genitalia. The type locality given by Radoszkowski is &quot;Siberia orientalis&quot;, and it has to be referred only to the male housed in the Radoszkowski collection. In the MNHM, we examined the rest of the type series listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mocsary, A" journalOrPublisher="Hungarian Academy of Science, Budapest" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refId="B85" refString="Mocsary, A, 1889. Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrarum Universi. Hungarian Academy of Science, Budapest" title="Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrarum Universi." year="1889">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
(1889)
</bibRefCitation>
: a female specimen collected in China (Ta-schian-sy). French (1986) designated this female as lectotype. However, this female belongs to a different species compared with the male collected in Siberia. The female lectotype is characterised by the very long pronotum (similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Abeille" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum longicolle" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicolle">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Hedychrum longicolle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and sharp and pointing out propodeal angles, while the male has a short pronotum and wide and triangular propodeal angles. A revision of the blue Asian species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Hedychrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is missing and urgently needed.
</paragraph>
